# Changelog
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [0.1.0] - 05/03/2026

### Added
- Multi-project requirements and tests management with project-scoped isolation.
- Requirement versioning with approval states (`draft`, `reviewed`, `approved`) and version diff endpoints/UI.
- Requirement comments on requirement/version detail views, including export support.
- Traceability matrix with suspect-link metadata and requirement/test relationship views.
- Immutable project baselines (snapshot of requirement versions + traceability) with baseline detail and diff-vs-current UI.
- Excel export/import workflows and ReqIF 1.2 import/export for current project and baseline snapshots.
- REST API coverage for requirements, tests, categories, applicability, matrix, baselines, and project-scoped endpoints.
- Bearer API tokens (including optional project scoping) for headless clients.
- Optional MCP server integration with read-only and controlled draft-write tool modes plus audit logging.
- Semantic search infrastructure with embedding storage, indexing queue, and reindex utility script.
- Audit/event logging for core user and entity operations.
- Group management with full CRUD operations and role-based member access control (Owner, Maintainer, Contributor, Viewer).
- Group-scoped project creation and listing with inline UI within group view page.
- Slug-based URL routing (`/:namespace/:projectSlug`) replacing numeric project IDs in all frontend routes.
- React pages for group management: list, create, view, edit, and member management.
- `POST /api/projects` endpoint for programmatic project creation with optional group assignment.

### Removed
- Legacy SSR-based group pages (static assets removed).

### Changed
- Frontend URL scheme from `/p/:projectId` to namespace-scoped `/:namespace/:projectSlug` across all pages.
- ProjectLayout to resolve projects dynamically by namespace and slug using `getProjectFromPath()` API fallback.
- All child pages updated to use `basePath` from outlet context instead of hardcoded numeric ID patterns.

### Fixed
